added.title: Halloween
added.description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
added.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: The So-Bad-Ical
added.description: When a new substitute shows up, KO and Dendy decide they need to get their old teacher back.

added.title: Are You Ready for Some Megafootball?!
added.description: Lakewood's Megafootball team takes on their rival in a big game.

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 1
added.description: Sgt. Night publicly criticizes Dr. Light's views on human & robot unity during a school assembly, invoking the ire of Fire Man and forcing Silicon City's newly minted hero, Mega Man, to intervene.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 2
added.description: Mega Man stops Fire Man by replicating his powers and fighting fire with fire. Unfortunately, Mega Man also learns that he can replicate a robot's mental state as well, and must get his own anger under control to win. Defeated, Fire Man reports back to his secret master, Sgt. Night!

added.title: Drilling Deep
added.description: At school, Aki struggles with the side effects of his newly replicated Drill Man schematics; later, as Mega Man, he learns to control his Fire Powers in thwarting Drill Man's assault on Skyraisers Inc.

added.title: Videodrone
added.description: Mega Man must stop Hypno Woman from turning the students and teachers at Silicon Central into her mindless drones.

added.title: Blaze of Glory
added.description: Mega Man and Suna must overcome a sibling dispute over what to do on their day off in order to stop Fire Man from overheating the city.

added.title: Nice on Ice
added.description: An "unscheduled" TV appearance not only lands Aki in hot water for missing class, but sets Ice Man on a misguided mission to "unite" (i.e. freeze together) every human and robot couple in the city!

added.title: Hard Times
added.description: Mega Man must stop Blasto Woman from plundering the Museum of the Hard Age and its cache of military grade weaponry.

added.title: Secrets Discovered
added.description: Secrets are revealed as Nya confronts the Samurai X imposter, Kai pursues the truth about his parents and the other Ninja desperately seek to locate and rescue Master Wu. But as usual, some answers only lead to more questions.

added.title: Out of the Fire and into the Boiling Sea
added.description: The Hands of Time blackmail Kai and Nya into using their combined elemental powers to retrieve the fourth and final Time Blade from the Boiling Sea with the promise the siblings can use its reversal power to save the quickly-fading Master Wu. Meanwhile, the Ninja and Cyrus Borg get unexpected help from Samurai X as they attempt to destroy the Hands of Time's time-travelling snake mech before it's operational.

added.title: Chad and the Marathon
added.description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Small World: Abra-Disaster Part 1
added.description: After defeating Mojo for the umpteenth time, the Powerpuff Girls are confident they are unstoppable.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: Quarantine
added.description: After a chemical spill, the girls and Mojo find themselves trapped together.

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Salamander
added.description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

added.title: Cleanliness Is Next to Grupliness
added.description: Grup has been stinking up the entire town of Rhyboflaven, but no matter how the Warriors try to lead the little dragon to water, they can't make him bathe!

added.title: Working for Scales
added.description: Princess Zange is sick and requires a dinosaur scale for a tea remedy, but King Rexxtopher is fiercely against the Warriors stepping foot inside his Dinosaur Kingdom to get it.

added.title: King of the Hill Part 2
added.description: The harried Autobots' Stunticon enemy proves more formidable and crafty than they anticipated, using his guided missiles to threaten a nuclear waste disposal site.

added.title: Five Fugitives
added.description: The Autobots' pursuit of Steeljaw hits an unexpected roadblock when Strongarm's old mentor DETECTIVE DROPFORGE arrives from Cybertron with orders to arrest the Bee Team!

added.title: Freedom Fighters
added.description: As the Bee Team struggles to liberate Cybertron from the Decepticon‑ controlled High Council, Optimus and his All Stars fight back the advance force of an Earth‑bound Cybertronian invasion!

added.title: Tenemos que vigilar
added.description: K.O. se une al Sr. Gar en una operación de vigilancia.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: No Mas Tarjetas de Poder
added.description: Cuando K.O. se da cuenta de que las Tarjetas de Poder excluyen a su amigo, no sabe qué hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: El joven y la logica
added.description: K.O. descubre cómo el Sr. Lógica llegó a la Plaza.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: De vuelta a la accion roja
added.description: Enid se alía a Acción Roja para enfrentarse a una amenaza del futuro.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Blurred
added.description: After his reckless actions cause the escape of a dangerous Sharkticon weapons engineer, Sideswipe goes out of his way to recapture the 'Con and prove his value to the Team in fear of getting replaced by a younger, and faster, newcomer -­‐‑Rescue Bot Blurr!

added.title: Bee Cool
added.description: Bee, trying to prove that he can be as cool as Sideswipe and his "intern" Blurr, struggles to lead the Autobots against two Stunticons who stole a trailer full of Cybertronian weapons.

added.title: Get a Clue
added.description: Strongarm flexes her detective muscles to solve a baffling series of Decepticon thefts. Can she stand up to her teammates, in order to bring a perp to justice?

added.title: Disordered Personalities
added.description: An experiment in combining accidentally causes the Autobots to swap personalities. Stuck in the wrong bodies, the team is called on a mission to defeat the Stunticons in a road race.

added.title: The Golden Knight
added.description: An ancient Cybertronian signal sends Bumblebee and chivalry-obsessed Fixit to a remote English island for a routine scouting mission that quickly turns into the duo's very own call to adventure!

added.title: Railroad Rage
added.description: The Bee Team races to keep the Stunticons from stealing a runaway train's fusion engine, and then prevent it from crashing into the Crown City Train Station.

added.title: Something He Ate
added.description: When Underbite eats part of the Autobots' GroundBridge, the Bee Team have to chase the teleporting 'Con through the desert, the forest, and even outer space!
